  "prompt": "What is the difference between a small bank and a payment bank?",
  "response": "Here are the key differences between a small bank and a payment bank:\n\nSmall Bank:\n1. Full banking services\n2. Can accept deposits of all amounts\n3. Provide traditional lending services\n4. Higher interest rates on deposits\n5. More comprehensive financial products\n6. Physical branch network\n7. Focus on local/regional markets\n8. Regulated by RBI under standard banking norms\n\nPayment Bank:\n1. Limited banking services\n2. Maximum deposit limit of \u20b91 lakh per customer\n3. Cannot provide traditional lending services\n4. Lower interest rates on deposits\n5. Focus on digital/mobile banking\n6. Minimal physical infrastructure\n7. Primarily serve unbanked/digital-first customers\n8. Specialized regulatory framework by RBI\n9. Can offer money transfer and bill payment services\n10. Often partnered with telecom or technology companies\n\nThe main difference is that payment banks are more technology-driven and have restricted operations compared to small banks, which offer comprehensive banking services.",
